{
  "explanation": "The defendant committed a significant breach of fiduciary duty by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. White-collar crimes of this nature require a penalty that reflects the severity of the theft and serves as a general deterrent. However, I have weighed this against substantial mitigating factors: the defendant lacks any prior criminal record and has already made good-faith efforts to partially repay the stolen funds. Considering these elements, a relatively short period of incarceration is appropriate to penalize the breach of trust, which will be followed by probation and a mandate to complete full restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
}
